{"lemma":"حَدَثِ","slug":"حَدَثِ","root":"ح.د.ث","root_slug":"ح-د-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-د-ث","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7308","n7314","n7315","n7316","n7317"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%AB%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to happen, to take place"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be new, to be young"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tell, to speak to (someone)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"novelty, innovation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"event, happening"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"misdeed"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"misfortune, mishap"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ordure, excrement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"young man, youth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"of a certain kind of military unit, militia","tags":["historical"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ḥdṯ-.\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *ḥdṯ- (“to be(come) new”). Cognate with Biblical Hebrew חִדֵּשׁ (ḥiddeš, “to renew”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7308","headword_ar":"حَدَثَ","root":"Hdv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuduwvN","text_ar":"حُدُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadaAvapN","text_ar":"حَدَاثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was new,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recent; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaduma","text_ar":"قَدُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, * A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came into existence; began to be; had a beginning; began,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"originated; existed newly, for the first time, not having been before:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, TA:) but when mentioned with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaduma","text_ar":"قَدُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haduva","text_ar":"حَدُثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K,) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*aniY maA qaduma wamaAHaduva","text_ar":"اَخَذَنِى مَا قَدُمَ وَمَاحَدُثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alx","text_ar":"الخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Old and new anxieties and thoughts"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came into my mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overcame me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old and new griefs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrows;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) the former saying occurring in a trad.: (TA:) the verb is not thus in any other case [in this sense]. (S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadava bihi EayobN","text_ar":"حَدَثَ بِهِ عَيْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, originated in him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, not having been before."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadava A^amorN","text_ar":"حَدَثَ اَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, originated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to pass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuduwvN","text_ar":"حُدُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of two kinds:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuduwvN zamaAniY~N","text_ar":"حُدُوثٌ زَمَانِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is A thing's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being preceded by non-existence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuduwvN *aAtiY~N","text_ar":"حُدُوثٌ ذَاتِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a thing's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being dependent upon another for its existence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadaAvapN","text_ar":"حَدَاثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuduwvapN","text_ar":"حُدُوثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as inf. ns. of which the verb, if they have one, is, accord. to analogy,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haduva","text_ar":"حَدُثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] relating to a man, signify The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being young;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or [as simple substs.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youthfulness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n7314","headword_ar":"حَدَثٌ","root":"Hdv","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A novelty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"new thing; an innovation; a thing not known before:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relating to El-Islám"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to matters of religious doctrine"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"practice"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh:) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN muHodavN","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ مُحْدَثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHodavaAtu AlA^umuwri","text_ar":"مُحْدَثَاتُ الاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHodavN","text_ar":"مُحْدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"innovations of people of erroneous opinions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inconsistent with the doctrines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"practices, of the just of preceding times:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is not known in revealed scripture, nor in the Sunneh, nor in the general conventional tenets of the doctors of the law:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in like manner,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an innovation that is disapproved, not agreeable with custom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usage, and not known in the Sunneh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=waY muHodavFA","text_ar":"ا=وَى مُحْدَثًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He entertained an innovation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he embraced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"held, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleased, with it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bore it patiently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=waY muHodivFA","text_ar":"ا=وَى مُحْدِثًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he entertained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harboured in his dwelling, a criminal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an offender, and protected him from retaliation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdivapN","text_ar":"حَادِثَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavaAnN","text_ar":"حَدَثَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in some copies of the S ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HidovaAn","text_ar":"حِدْثَان","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudovaY","text_ar":"حُدْثَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An accident, an event, a hap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a casualty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and generally"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evil accident"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, a mishap, a misfortune, a disaster, a calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affliction"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) [the most common of these words is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdivapN","text_ar":"حَادِثَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its pl.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAdivu","text_ar":"حَوَادِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is more common than the sing.:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHodaAvN","text_ar":"اَحْدَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHodaAvu Ald~ahori","text_ar":"اَحْدَاثُ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAdivuhu","text_ar":"حَوَادِثُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HidovaAnuhu","text_ar":"حِدْثَانُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or, as is said by Fr and others, this last is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavaAnuhu","text_ar":"حَدَثَانُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The accidents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"casualties, of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the evil accidents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calamities, of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAdivu","text_ar":"حَوَادِثُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs used as a sing., said to be put by poetic license for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavaAnN","text_ar":"حَدَثَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and this latter is also used [as a pl.] for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAdivu","text_ar":"حَوَادِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so say Az and AAF: and it is said to be a noun in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAdivu Ald~ahori","text_ar":"حَوَادِثُ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawaAy^ibu Ald~ahori","text_ar":"نَوَايِبُ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to Fr, the Arabs say, [using it as a pl.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholakatonaA","text_ar":"اَهْلَكَتْنَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadavaAnu","text_ar":"الحَدَثَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The accidents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil accidents, of time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune, destroyed us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadavaAni","text_ar":"الحَدَثَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", making it dual of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and meaning thereby"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night and day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as they say [in the same sense]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljadiydaAni","text_ar":"الجَدِيدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmalawaAni","text_ar":"المَلَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a term applied by Sb to The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSodar","text_ar":"مَصْدَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"infinitive noun"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because all"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mSAdir","text_ar":"مصادِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"are [significant of] accidents [considered as subsisting in, or proceding from, agents]: and the pl. which he assigns to it in this sense is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHodaAvN","text_ar":"اَحْدَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"voiding of ordure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaking of wind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibodaA='N","text_ar":"اـِبْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legal impurity that forbids,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prevents, one's performing prayer &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state annulling legal purity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHodaAvN","text_ar":"اَحْدَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [See 4.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliY~N","text_ar":"وَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain following that called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasomiY~","text_ar":"وَسْمِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (L:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aHodaAvu","text_ar":"الاَحْدَاثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadavu","text_ar":"الحَدَثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rains of the commencement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first part, of the year."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Young,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man, (A, * L, Msb, *) and to a horse or an ass or the like, and a camel, and, accord. to IAar, to a mountain-goat: (L:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHodaAvN","text_ar":"اَحْدَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudovaAnN","text_ar":"حُدْثَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN HadavN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, S, L, &c.,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadiyvu","text_ar":"حَدِيثُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~in~i","text_ar":"السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, S, A, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadavu Als~in~","text_ar":"حَدَثُ السِّنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, K, [but this is by some disallowed, as will be seen below,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K:) and in the pl. sense you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gilomaAnN A^aHodaAvN","text_ar":"غِلْمَانٌ اَحْدَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudovaAnN","text_ar":"حُدْثَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijaAlN A^aHodaAvu","text_ar":"رِجَالٌ اَحْدَاثُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~in~i","text_ar":"السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudovaAnu Als~in~i","text_ar":"حُدْثَانُ السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or these, as is implied above, are not allowable,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudavaA='u Als~in~i","text_ar":"حُدَثَا=ءُ السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISd, TA.) J says, [in the S,] if you mention the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~","text_ar":"سِنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~in~i","text_ar":"السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadiyvu","text_ar":"حَدِيثُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Young of tooth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and IDrst says, the vulgar say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hadavu Als~in~i","text_ar":"هُوَ حَدَثُ السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hdyv Als~in~i","text_ar":"حديث السِّنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it is a mistake; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet applied to the man himself, and is originally an inf. n.; one should not apply it as an epithet to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~","text_ar":"سِنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Diros","text_ar":"ضِرْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAb","text_ar":"ناب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an epithet applied to anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","S","A","K","KT","L","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n7315","headword_ar":"حَدُثٌ","root":"Hdv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence; each in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7316","headword_ar":"حَدِثٌ","root":"Hdv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence; each in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7317","headword_ar":"حَدِثٌ","root":"Hdv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadavN","text_ar":"حَدَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}